00:00:09.870 --> 00:00:11.190
Concept explanation.

00:00:11.670 --> 00:00:13.650
So what is this big term?

00:00:13.650 --> 00:00:14.940
Financial inclusion.

00:00:15.420 --> 00:00:19.860
Think of it as sending a formal
invitation to everyone to join

00:00:19.860 --> 00:00:21.630
the country's economic party.

00:00:22.110 --> 00:00:25.650
It refers to the process
of ensuring that everyone.

00:00:25.750 --> 00:00:30.850
Especially our vulnerable groups, like the
weaker sections and low income families,

00:00:31.030 --> 00:00:37.000
gets access to financial services and
not just any access mind you, but timely,

00:00:37.180 --> 00:00:39.940
adequate, and at an affordable cost.

00:00:40.360 --> 00:00:44.590
The goal is to bring the unbanked
and underbanked folks into

00:00:44.590 --> 00:00:46.330
the formal financial system.

00:00:46.629 --> 00:00:51.129
We are talking about essential
services like savings accounts, credit

00:00:51.280 --> 00:00:53.140
insurance, and sending money home.

00:00:53.940 --> 00:00:59.040
It's all about promoting inclusive
growth, enabling every single person to

00:00:59.040 --> 00:01:04.980
participate in the economic mainstream,
and most importantly, improve their lives.

00:01:06.015 --> 00:01:07.425
Real world relevance.

00:01:07.695 --> 00:01:11.595
Now you might ask, sir, why
is this so important for me?

00:01:11.895 --> 00:01:16.425
Well, my friend, understanding
this is absolutely crucial because

00:01:16.455 --> 00:01:20.865
it directly impacts your ability
to serve a diverse customer base

00:01:21.045 --> 00:01:24.795
and implement government schemes
effectively when you are in a bank.

00:01:25.255 --> 00:01:29.515
This knowledge helps you identify
and address the financial needs

00:01:29.515 --> 00:01:31.435
of people who have been left out.

00:01:31.825 --> 00:01:36.175
It's a win-win, contributing to
the bank's social objectives, and

00:01:36.235 --> 00:01:37.914
of course its business growth.

