00:02:33.145 --> 00:02:35.815
Now let's meet the
superstars of this show.

00:02:36.235 --> 00:02:42.565
First, there's PM JDY or Phan Ri
Jhan Yna, the National Mission to

00:02:42.565 --> 00:02:44.665
give everyone access to banking.

00:02:45.145 --> 00:02:47.185
Then we have the insurance duo.

00:02:47.550 --> 00:02:55.200
P-M-S-B-Y or Phan Man, Akima Yo, which
is an accident insurance scheme and pm

00:02:55.200 --> 00:03:02.670
JJ BY, the Phan man Jo, which is a life
insurance scheme for old age planning,

00:03:02.790 --> 00:03:08.250
we have PY, the Utter pension Yona,
mainly for workers in the unorganized

00:03:08.250 --> 00:03:10.650
sector to fuel small businesses.

00:03:10.770 --> 00:03:15.450
There's Mudra, the Microunits
Development and Refinance Agency Limited.

00:03:15.835 --> 00:03:20.425
Which helps banks lend to
microenterprises to reach the last mile.

00:03:20.545 --> 00:03:24.625
We have our heroes, the business
correspondents or bcs, who

00:03:24.625 --> 00:03:28.045
are agents providing banking
services in remote areas.

00:03:28.435 --> 00:03:32.935
And the foundation of it all is
financial literacy, which is simply

00:03:33.055 --> 00:03:37.829
educating people about all these
wonderful products, methods of solving.

00:03:38.575 --> 00:03:40.975
To tackle questions, think strategically.

00:03:41.275 --> 00:03:45.835
Use objective driven analysis,
meaning for any scheme, first,

00:03:45.835 --> 00:03:47.275
figure out its main goal.

00:03:47.635 --> 00:03:51.025
Is it about universal
access or social security?

00:03:51.385 --> 00:03:55.770
Next, use beneficiary identification
to pinpoint who the scheme is for.

00:03:56.390 --> 00:04:00.050
Are we talking about unbanked
households or small entrepreneurs?

00:04:00.745 --> 00:04:02.725
Then understand the mechanism.

00:04:02.995 --> 00:04:07.915
Grasp how the scheme actually works, like
zero balance accounts or microcredit.

00:04:08.274 --> 00:04:10.524
Also, try some impact assessment.

00:04:10.885 --> 00:04:14.185
Consider the broader effects
on poverty and economic growth.

00:04:14.605 --> 00:04:19.375
Finally, master challenge solution
pairing for every challenge, like lack

00:04:19.375 --> 00:04:23.875
of awareness, know the corresponding
solution, shortcuts and smart techniques.

00:04:24.489 --> 00:04:25.809
Want some smart techniques.

00:04:25.869 --> 00:04:28.869
Of course, you do use acronym association.

00:04:29.109 --> 00:04:34.450
For instance, P-M-J-D-Y becomes
Han Ana or People's Wealth Scheme.

00:04:34.809 --> 00:04:36.940
Also practice keyword linking.

00:04:37.239 --> 00:04:41.289
The moment you see no frills account,
your brain should immediately connect

00:04:41.289 --> 00:04:43.539
it to basic savings, bank deposit.

00:04:44.359 --> 00:04:48.830
Another great trick is categorization
group schemes by their purpose.

00:04:49.130 --> 00:04:53.659
For instance, insurance includes
P-M-S-B-Y and P-M-J-J-B-Y.

00:04:54.049 --> 00:04:59.719
Pension means a PY credit means mudra,
and in multiple choice questions,

00:04:59.900 --> 00:05:04.820
always use the elimination strategy to
remove options that are obviously wrong.

00:05:05.330 --> 00:05:07.460
Common mistakes and misconceptions.

00:05:08.119 --> 00:05:10.520
Alright, let's talk
about the common traps.

00:05:11.050 --> 00:05:12.880
Please avoid confusing schemes.

00:05:13.090 --> 00:05:16.870
Don't mix up the features of
P-M-S-B-Y and P-M-J-J-B-Y.

00:05:17.409 --> 00:05:20.380
Also, never ignore the
affordable cost part.

00:05:20.740 --> 00:05:25.300
Financial inclusion is about reasonably
priced services, not just access.

00:05:25.780 --> 00:05:28.750
A big mistake is underestimating
technology's role.

00:05:28.755 --> 00:05:32.110
Digital banking and adhar
are game changers here.

00:05:32.530 --> 00:05:34.330
Don't believe it's only for the poor.

00:05:34.580 --> 00:05:40.310
As the aim is to integrate everyone, and
please don't focus only on urban areas.

00:05:40.549 --> 00:05:44.870
Financial inclusion is hugely focused
on rural and semi-urban regions.

